% We test with the GCD function again, this time going to LaTeX
Wow this is LaTeX text.
Now we get this beautiful definition:
<<<
gcd : N x N -> Z+
gcd(a, b) := {
    a               if b = 0
    gcd(b, a mod b) otherwise
} where a >= b
>>>
And we can evaluate:
{{{gcd(12, 9)}}}, {{{gcd(27, 14)}}} and {{{gcd(28, 14)}}}.